        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-16 01:58:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Build Failed\n > \n > https://jenkins.onap.org/job/policy-drools-applications-master-verify-java/874/\n > : FAILURE\n > \n > maven-compiler-plugin testCompile goal has failed to compile tests.\n > Please review the compilation issues in the log ( https://jenkins.onap.org/job/policy-drools-applications-master-verify-java/874/\n > )\n > \n > Logs: https://logs.onap.org/production/vex-yul-ecomp-jenkins-1/policy-drools-applications-master-verify-java/874\n\nThe build failed due cross project dependency. I modified the code in drools-pdp in prev commit., and these objects are used in test cases of drools-applications, and hence the test class failed to compile. \ni did not take care of this cross compiling. actually this is first time i encountered the case, where a class defined in drools-application is used outside of this project in another project such as drools-pdp. \nIs this type of dependency valid ? in which case, if we change a class in one project, we might have to compile all the other projects.",
        "patchset_number": 1
